## Getting Started

```bash
# Install dependencies
bun install

# Run checks
bun run check

# Run tests
bun run test
```

## Development

### Adding a new package

Use [summon-package](https://www.npmjs.com/package/@canonical/summon-package) to scaffold a new package:

```bash
bunx summon package
```

### Scripts

| Script | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| `bun run build` | Build all packages |
| `bun run build:all` | Build all packages and artifacts |
| `bun run check` | Run linting and type checks |
| `bun run check:fix` | Auto-fix linting issues |
| `bun run test` | Run all tests |
| `bun run test:coverage` | Run tests with coverage |
| `bun run publish:status` | Compare local vs. registry versions |
| `bun run special:clean` | Clean all build artifacts and dependencies |

### Releasing

Releases are managed via the `tag.yml` GitHub Actions workflow:

1. Go to **Actions** > **Update package versions**
2. Select a release type (experimental, alpha, beta, rc, stable)
3. Run the workflow

This will bump versions, generate changelogs, tag, and publish to npm.

